snippet.textDisplay: I think Billie deserved her Brit awards. One day people will understand that screaming and be loud doesn’t automatically mean you’re a good singer. Harry and Ariana are too generic. Billie is different and people obviously like that. She can turn her hand at anything. Her vocals in Six Feet Above, Ocean Eyes, Lovely and When the Party’s Over are so smooth and she has a fantastic tone. When the Party’s Over is 2 octaves high. Billie can also write/ produce catchy upbeat songs that get heads turning like bad guy and burry a friend. Her brother Finneas puts a lot of effort and skill into the backing tracks and sings occasionally in background. Billie also sings whilst dancing and running around on stage which is a skill in itself. I think people are jealous of her success.

He's one of the few artists who can really bring you to other places with the emotions he gives to every single word he sings. I'm one of those people who do not just hear the music or listen to it but who really lives and feel it. Thank you Harry for bringing me to amazing places when you give everything you have on stage. 2020 doesn't seem like the best year for you yet, but remain strong and let go when you have to, that's what makes us human.
